  <h2>Step 2: Get a Health Report</h2>

  <p>For a broader view, run the health report:</p>

  <pre><code>npx ahoybuoy show health</code></pre>

  <p>This shows your overall design system health score and worst offenders.</p>

  <h2>Step 3: Fix Drift Automatically</h2>

  <p>See what Buoy can fix for you:</p>

  <pre><code># Preview fixes (dry run)
buoy drift fix --dry-run

# Apply fixes to files
buoy drift fix --apply</code></pre>

  <p>Buoy replaces hardcoded values with matching design tokens, with configurable confidence levels.</p>

  <h2>Step 4: Set Up Config (Optional)</h2>

  <p>For ongoing use, dock Buoy into your project:</p>

  <pre><code>buoy dock config</code></pre>

  <p>This creates a <code>.buoy.yaml</code> config file with auto-detected settings for your project.</p>

